cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with time synchronization in sensor networks. It could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it involves synchronization over multiple hops. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it deals with improving synchronization performance. The paper also involves analysis and simulation, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) respectively.
